to be used against the Light, and that he belonged, in truth, fully to Hate.<br>
<br>
Well, imagine her surprise when she asked Dinian to recant my words and he responded to her with a smile and cold silence.  She of course attmepted to do away with him.  It was a glorious sight to see Dinian's Hatred released upon the creature, as he channeled the dark power into his blades and destroyed it in short order.<br>
<br>
Yes, the power of Hatred is still strong in the Hounds and their task of espionage is nearly completed.  Soon, when they assassinate the leadership of that Fellowship of Fools, they will return to our Halls with the right to be re-named Tiller, perhaps earning the priveleged rank of Harrower once they are re-affirmed in their true path.  Until then, Faeolin is correct - only those with insignia may be called Tiller - but in their hearts, the Hounds have never strayed from Hate's path.  I cannot and will not disclose the orders they were given - or by whom - but when their task is completed, they will be returned to Hate's family with no loss in standing or status.<br>
<br>
The baying of the Hounds of Hate draws nigh.  Woe to the children of the Light.<br>
<br>
Nospiratus K'Thalion<br>
Prophet of the Divine Hate <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ufaeolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faeolin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dread Overlord</span><br>  Posts: 588<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/23/02 3:22:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A wish to join</span><hr size=1> Then I stand corrected, and will say no more.<br>
